Select API Specification

The Select API provides read access to map data stored on a layer.

The Select API provides read access to map data stored on a layer.

The API supports requests specifying the branch and versionTo of map data to read. This API supports three main entities: Feature, Association, and Attribute.

Select is a Java library with a minimal set of dependencies needed to start reading data from a layer. It is meant to be used by developers using the CMR platform. For example, the API can be used for exporting data to custom formats. This API is also exposed to the transformation plugin and developers can use the API as a data access tool for both parent and child layers.

The API is model independent, which means there is no compile time nor runtime dependencies needed to read data described in any model. Select API is designed to be a simple yet efficient tool for accessing data and allows developers to build more complex domain driven access layers on top of it for operations such as object mapping and lazy loading. The generic approach to return types minimizes HTTP traffic footprint and improves performance of the API.
